<li id="cite_note-49"><span class="mw-cite-backlink noprint"><a href="#cite_ref-49">↑</a> </span><span class="reference-text"><span class="ouvrage" id="Dulles2005"><span class="ouvrage" id="Avery_Dulles2005"><abbr class="abbr indicateur-langue" title="Langue : anglais">(en)</abbr> <a href="/wiki/Avery_Dulles" title="Avery Dulles">Avery Dulles</a>, «&#160;<cite style="font-style:normal" lang="en">Development or Reversal?</cite>&#160;», <i><span class="lang-en" lang="en">First Things</span></i>,&#8206; <time class="nowrap" datetime="2005-10" data-sort-value="2005-10">octobre 2005</time> <small style="line-height:1em;">(<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.firstthings.com/article/2005/10/development-or-reversal">lire en ligne</a>)</small><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Development+or+Reversal%3F&amp;rft.jtitle=First+Things&amp;rft.aulast=Dulles&amp;rft.aufirst=Avery&amp;rft.date=2005-10&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.firstthings.com%2Farticle%2F2005%2F10%2Fdevelopment-or-reversal&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Ffr.wikipedia.org%3AAbolition+de+l'esclavage"></span></span></span>&#160;:<blockquote><p>«&#160;<span class="lang-en" lang="en">In 1866 the Holy Office, in response to an inquiry from Africa, ruled that although slavery (servitus) was undesirable, it was not per se opposed to natural or divine law. This ruling pertained to the kind of servitude that was customary in certain parts of Africa at the time.</span>&#160;»</p></blockquote></span>
